companyProfile.companyDescription: JSW Steel Limited is an India-based holding company. The Company is primarily engaged in the business of manufacturing and sale of iron and steel products. It is an integrated manufacturer of a diverse range of steel products with its manufacturing facilities located at Vijayanagar Works in Karnataka, Dolvi Works in Maharashtra and Salem works in Tamil Nadu and also in the United States of America and Italy. It also has a plate and coil mill division in Anjar, Gujarat. It offers a gamut of steel products that includes hot rolled, cold rolled, bare and pre-painted galvanized and Galvalume, thermo-mechanically treated (TMT) rebars, wire rods and special steel. It offers a range of coated steel products that provide anti-corrosive properties. It serves multiple brands with its coated steel products, including GI (Vishwas), GL (Silveron), Color Coated (Everglow, Colouron+, Pragati+) and OEM products (Radiance). Its subsidiaries include JSW Steel (USA) Inc., Purest Energy, LLC, and others.

recentNews.headline: For steel companies, Q4 was an inflexion point as prices, demand firm up
recentNews.intro: Firm steel prices and a decline in imports are expected to further improve the profitability of four integrated steel players JSW Steel, Tata Steel, Steel Authority of India and Jindal Steel moving ahead
recentNews.imagecaption: The combined Ebitda of JSW Steel, Tata Steel, Steel Authority of India and Jindal Steel rose only marginally by 1% during the quarter. (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: Tata Steel, JSW Energy to HDFC AMC: 5 stocks to trade ex-dividend today
recentNews.intro: Dividend Stocks: Tata Steel, JSW Energy, HDFC AMC, Container Corporation of India and Bank of Baroda are among the five stocks that will trade ex-dividend today.
recentNews.imagecaption: Dividend Stocks:  5 Stocks to trade Ex dividend today

recentNews.headline: Parliamentary panel to recommend fresh set of changes to insolvency code
recentNews.intro: A Supreme Court ruling exposing legal gaps in India?s bankruptcy process has prompted a legislative rethink. A parliamentary committee is now finalizing reform proposals to address delays, low recoveries, and jurisdictional grey zones under the IBC.
recentNews.imagecaption: The ministry of corporate affairs is currently working on amendments to the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code to remove ambiguity. (File Photo: Mint)

recentNews.headline: JSW Steel, Vedanta, Tata Steel and other metal stocks drop up to 2% as Trump doubles tariffs to 50%
recentNews.intro: Indian metal stocks fell up to 2%, with major companies like Lloyds Metals & Energy and Vedanta facing significant losses. Global trade tensions, particularly US tariffs on steel and aluminum, are affecting market sentiment and raising concerns over future metal demand.
recentNews.imagecaption: JSW Steel, Vedanta, Tata Steel and other metal stocks drop up to 2% as trade tensions resurface

recentNews.headline: Q4 results today: IRCTC, Deepak Nitrate, SAIL, Cummins, Bata India, Nuvama Wealth, 3M, Natco Pharma, Finolex on May 28
recentNews.intro: Q4 results on May 28: IRCTC, Deepak Nitrate, SAIL, Cummins, Bata, Nuvama Wealth, 3M, Natco Pharma, and Finolex Cables are among 428 firms to release their earnings report today.
recentNews.imagecaption: Q4 results today, on May 28: IRCTC, Deepak Nitrate, SAIL, Cummins, Bata, 3M, Nuvama Wealth, Natco Pharma, JSW Holdings, and Finolex Cables are among at least 428 companies scheduled to release their earnings report.

recentNews.headline: NCLT puts Bhushan Power liquidation on hold till August after SC order
recentNews.intro: The Supreme Court on 26 May granted interim relief to JSW Steel, which had sought a pause on the BPSL liquidation proceedings to file a review petition challenging the top court?s 2 May verdict.
recentNews.imagecaption: On 2 May, the Supreme Court quashed JSW Steel's  ?19,300 crore resolution plan for Bhushan Power and Steel. (Image: Pixabay)

recentNews.headline: JSW Steel share price: Should you Buy or Sell the stock post Q4 Results?
recentNews.intro: Stock Market Today: JSW Steel share price gained more than 2% in the intraday trades on Monday post Q4 results that were declared on Friday, but after the market hours: Should you Buy or Sell the stock post Q4 Results?
recentNews.imagecaption: Stock Market Today: JSW Steel share price gains

recentNews.headline: Supreme Court orders status quo on Bhushan Power liquidation, allows JSW Steel to file review
recentNews.intro: The Supreme Court has halted the liquidation proceedings of Bhushan Power and Steel Ltd, allowing JSW Steel to file a review petition against a previous ruling that invalidated its  ?19,300 crore resolution plan. The NCLT has been directed to keep the matter pending until the court decides.
recentNews.imagecaption: The Supreme Court's decision to allow JSW Steel to file a review petition is significant not just from a legal standpoint but also due to the financial and strategic importance of Bhushan Power and Steel to the company's domestic operations. (Reuters)

recentNews.headline: JSW Steel eyes a resurgence in overseas operations, lower costs in India in FY26
recentNews.intro: While relatively small in scale compared to its sprawling domestic steelmaking empire, the cash hemorrhage at the company's overseas units in the US and Italy had been eating into its consolidated margins.
recentNews.imagecaption: JSW Steel?s joint managing director Jayant Acharya. (Reuters)
